00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:20.890
to this International Poetry
event which is being co-sponsored

00:00:20.890 --> 00:00:24.070
by the Poetry and Literature
Center and the Hispanic Division.

00:00:24.070 --> 00:00:28.190
And I want to thank Anya Creightney
for helping this wonderful event

00:00:28.190 --> 00:00:31.280
and also Talia Guzman Gonzalez.

00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:34.270
I would like to ask you all to
turn off your electronic devices

00:00:34.270 --> 00:00:38.070
so we don't interfere with
the wonderful happenings.

00:00:38.070 --> 00:00:41.680
It is indeed a great please to
introduce today Raúl Zurita,

00:00:41.680 --> 00:00:44.270
an outstanding Chilean
poet who began

00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:46.190
as an engineer and a mathematician.

00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:51.840
Can you hear?

00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:53.900
Raúl Zurita began,
right, as an engineer

00:00:53.900 --> 00:00:57.580
and became an important poet
at the age of 22 in Chile.

00:00:57.580 --> 00:01:02.110
He's written many works, among
them Purgatorio, Anteparaiso,

00:01:02.110 --> 00:01:06.530
Canto a Su Amor Desaparecido,
La Vida Nueva, and Zurita.

00:01:06.530 --> 00:01:09.870 position:56%
Altogether, 35 hits in the Library
of Congress catalog, which includes,

00:01:09.870 --> 00:01:12.720
of course, anthologies and
mentions in other works.

00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:14.930
He's also a very well known artist,

00:01:14.930 --> 00:01:18.800
having begun El Colectivo
Acciones de Arte in Chile

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:22.900
to oppose the government of
Augusto Pinochet in Chile.

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:26.260
He has won the Chilean
National Book Award,

00:01:26.260 --> 00:01:31.080
Premio Nacional de Literatura de
Chile, the Pablo Neruda Award,

00:01:31.080 --> 00:01:35.080
Premio Casa de las Americas,
and also many honorary degrees

00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:40.060
from universities in addition
to the Guggenheim Fellowship.

00:01:40.060 --> 00:01:43.350
And then with us will be his
translator, Anna Deeny Morales,

00:01:43.350 --> 00:01:45.430
a literary critic and translator.

00:01:45.430 --> 00:01:48.700
Her translations of Raúl
Zurita's works include Purgatory,

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:53.890 position:56%
Dreams of Kurosawa, Sky Below, and a
volume of selected poems forthcoming

00:01:53.890 --> 00:01:55.190
from Northwestern University.

00:01:55.190 --> 00:01:57.150
She is currently a professor
at Georgetown University.

00:01:57.150 --> 00:01:58.950
Raúl.

